55011, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjk1NTAxMQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/955011?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulrobello", "html_url": "https://github.com/paulrobello", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulrobello/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulrobello/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulrobello/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulrobello/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulrobello/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulrobello/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulrobello/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulrobello/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulrobello/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2025-11-18T06:45:48Z", "updated_at": "2025-11-18T06:47:40Z", "closed_at": "2025-11-18T06:45:58Z", "author_association": "OWNER", "active_lock_reason": null, "draft": false, "pull_request": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/paulrobello/par-term-emu-core-rust/pulls/8", "html_url": "https://github.com/paulrobello/par-term-emu-core-rust/pull/8", "diff_url": "https://github.com/paulrobello/par-term-emu-core-rust/pull/8.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/paulrobello/par-term-emu-core-rust/pull/8.patch", "merged_at": "2025-11-18T06:45:58Z"}, "body": "Implements comprehensive tmux control mode protocol parsing and integration, allowing the terminal to act as a tmux control mode client (tmux -C/-CC).\r\n\r\n## Features Added\r\n\r\n### Core Module (`src/tmux_control.rs`)\r\n- Complete tmux control protocol parser with 25+ notification types\r\n- Support for all protocol messages: %begin, %end, %error, %output, %exit, etc.\r\n- Octal escape sequence unescaping for output data\r\n- Line buffering for incomplete data handling\r\n- Comprehensive test coverage with 20+ unit tests\r\n\r\n### Terminal Integration\r\n- Added `tmux_parser` and `tmux_notifications` fields to Terminal struct\r\n- Modified `process()` to route data through tmux parser when enabled\r\n- Separate VTE processing for terminal output vs control messages\r\n- Methods to enable/disable control mode and access notifications\r\n\r\n### Python Bindings\r\n- `PyTmuxNotification` type with all notification fields exposed\r\n- Terminal methods: `set_tmux_control_mode()`, `is_tmux_control_mode()`\r\n- Notification access: `get_tmux_notifications()`, `drain_tmux_notifications()`\r\n- Helper methods: `has_tmux_notifications()`, `clear_tmux_notifications()`\r\n\r\n### Documentation\r\n- Updated README.md to list tmux control protocol in Modern Features\r\n- Inline documentation for all public APIs\r\n- Usage examples in docstrings\r\n\r\n## Protocol Compliance\r\n\r\nImplements the tmux control mode protocol as specified in the tmux wiki:\r\n- Command output wrapping with %begin/%end/%error\r\n- Asynchronous notifications (window/pane/session events)\r\n- Flow control support (%pause, %continue, %extended-output)\r\n- Subscription change notifications\r\n- Client detachment and exit handling\r\n\r\n## Testing\r\n\r\n- 20+ Rust unit tests for parser functionality\r\n- Parser correctly handles all notification types\r\n- Octal escape sequence conversion tested\r\n- Incomplete line buffering verified\r\n- Terminal integration tested\r\n\r\nThis enables applications to interact with tmux programmatically through the control protocol, supporting use cases like:\r\n- Terminal multiplexer integration\r\n- Automated tmux session management\r\n- Custom tmux control interfaces\r\n- Integration testing with tmux\r\n\r\nCloses feature request for tmux control protocol support.", "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/paulrobello/par-term-emu-core-rust/issues/8/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/paulrobello/par-term-emu-core-rust/issues/8/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/paulrobello/par-term-emu-core-rust/issues/7", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/paulrobello/par-term-emu-core-rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/paulrobello/par-term-emu-core-rust/issues/7/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/paulrobello/par-term-emu-core-rust/issues/7/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/paulrobello/par-term-emu-core-rust/issues/7/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/paulrobello/par-term-emu-core-rust/pull/7", "id": 3636327308, "node_id": "PR_kwDOQWY_T860A_q9", "number": 7, "title": "Add VT520 terminal sequence support", "user": {"login": "paulrobello", "id": 955011, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjk1NTAxMQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/955011?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulrobello", "html_url": "https://github.com/paulrobello", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulrobello/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulrobello/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulrobello/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulrobello/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulrobello/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulrobello/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulrobello/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulrobello/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulrobello/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2025-11-18T06:10:18Z", "updated_at": "2025-11-18T06:11:52Z", "closed_at": "2025-11-18T06:10:27Z", "author_association": "OWNER", "active_lock_reason": null, "draft": false, "pull_request": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/paulrobello/par-term-emu-core-rust/pulls/7", "html_url": "https://github.com/paulrobello/par-term-emu-core-rust/pull/7", "diff_url": "https://github.com/paulrobello/par-term-emu-core-rust/pull/7.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/paulrobello/par-term-emu-core-rust/pull/7.patch", "merged_at": "2025-11-18T06:10:27Z"}, "body": "Implement VT520 terminal emulation with conformance level control and bell volume management. This adds support for the final DEC VT terminal level, providing full backward compatibility with VT100/220/320/420.\r\n\r\nKey Features:\r\n- Conformance level tracking (VT100/220/320/420/520)\r\n- DECSCL (Set Conformance Level) - CSI Pl ; Pc \" p\r\n- DECSWBV (Set Warning-Bell Volume) - CSI Ps SP t\r\n- DECSMBV (Set Margin-Bell Volume) - CSI Ps SP u\r\n- Dynamic Device Attributes reporting based on conformance level\r\n\r\nImplementation Details:\r\n- New conformance_level module with ConformanceLevel enum\r\n- Terminal fields: conformance_level, warning_bell_volume, margin_bell_volume\r\n- Updated Device Attributes (DA) to report VT520 (id=65) by default\r\n- DA response varies dynamically based on current conformance level\r\n\r\nPython API:\r\n- conformance_level() - Get current level (1-5)\r\n- conformance_level_name() - Get level name string\r\n- set_conformance_level(level, c1_mode) - Change conformance level\r\n- warning_bell_volume() / set_warning_bell_volume(volume)\r\n- margin_bell_volume() / set_margin_bell_volume(volume)\r\n\r\nTesting:\r\n- 15 comprehensive tests for VT520 features\r\n- Tests for conformance level switching\r\n- Tests for Device Attributes reporting\r\n- Tests for bell volume controls\r\n- Tests for feature support checking\r\n\r\nDocumentation:\r\n- Updated README.md to mention VT520 support\r\n- Added VT520 section to VT_FEATURE_PARITY.md\r\n- Documented DECSCL, DECSWBV, DECSMBV sequences\r\n- Updated compatibility matrix\r\n\r\nAll changes compile cleanly with no clippy warnings.", "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/paulrobello/par-term-emu-core-rust/issues/7/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/paulrobello/par-term-emu-core-rust/issues/7/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/paulrobello/par-term-emu-core-rust/issues/6", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/paulrobello/par-term-emu-core-rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/paulrobello/par-term-emu-core-rust/issues/6/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/paulrobello/par-term-emu-core-rust/issues/6/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/paulrobello/par-term-emu-core-rust/issues/6/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/paulrobello/par-term-emu-core-rust/pull/6", "id": 3635872578, "node_id": "PR_kwDOQWY_T86z_eFg", "number": 6, "title": "test: add 17 new tests for grid rectangle operations", "user": {"login": "paulrobello", "id": 955011, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjk1NTAxMQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/955011?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulrobello", "html_url": "https://github.com/paulrobello", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulrobello/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulrobello/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulrobello/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulrobello/starred